(41, 12, 7, 23, 53, 7, 8, 'let us kill him', 'Connection of Rejection and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection and suffering in both passages. In Mark, the husbandmen plot to kill the heir, while Isaiah describes the suffering servant who is oppressed and silent before his execution.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
